net.engio.daoism.dao

Class TypedDao<K extends Serializable,E extends Persistent<K>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.engio.daoism.dao.TypedDao<K,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    K -
    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ITypedDao<K,E>

    public abstract class TypedDao<K extends Serializable,E extends Persistent<K>>
extends Object
implements ITypedDao<K,E>
    The typed dao is the default implementation of the ITypedDao interface. It is merely a thin wrapper that delegates all operations to an underlying instance of IPersistenceProvider. It is completely technology agnostic since all technology specific operations are implemented in the delegate IPersistenceProvider. It's main function is to parametrize all calls to the IPersistenceProvider with the necessary domain and key classes
    Author:
    Benjamin Diedrichsen
